### Description

Fixes https://github.com/apache/cloudstack/issues/5290
Fixes incorrect count returned in listServiceOfferings and listDiskOfferings caused by filtering records in the manager rather than directly in the database

### Types of changes

- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to change)
- [ ] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)
- [x] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)
- [ ] Enhancement (improves an existing feature and functionality)
- [ ] Cleanup (Code refactoring and cleanup, that may add test cases)

#### Bug Severity

- [ ] BLOCKER
- [ ] Critical
- [ ] Major
- [x] Minor
- [ ] Trivial

### How Has This Been Tested?

Previously, would give the wrong count
```
  "count": 7,
```


Domains : `/dom1/(sub1, sub2, sub3)`
Calling listOfferings as a dom1 user
```
(dom1) ðŸ± > list serviceofferings filter=name,domain listall=true
{
  "count": 4,
  "serviceoffering": [
    {
      "name": "Small Instance" <- common
    },
    {
      "name": "Medium Instance" <- common
    },
    {
      "domain": "ROOT",
      "name": "root-o1" <- parent
    },
    {
      "domain": "dom1",
      "name": "dom1-o1" <- mine
    }
  ]
}
```

Calling listOfferings as a dom1/sub1 user
```
{
  "count": 6,
  "serviceoffering": [
    {
      "name": "Small Instance" <- common
    },
    {
      "name": "Medium Instance"
    },
    {
      "domain": "ROOT",
      "name": "root-o1" <- ancestor
    },
    {
      "domain": "dom1",
      "name": "dom1-o1" <- parent
    },
    {
      "domain": "sub1",
      "name": "sub1-o1" <- mine
    },
    {
      "domain": "sub1,sub2",
      "name": "common"  <- common
    }
  ]
}
```

With isrecursive
```
(domadmin) ðŸ± > list serviceofferings filter=name,domain isrecursive=true listall=true
{
  "count": 7,
  "serviceoffering": [
    {
      "name": "Small Instance" <- common
    },
    {
      "name": "Medium Instance"
    },
    {
      "domain": "ROOT",
      "name": "root-o1" <- parent
    },
    {
      "domain": "dom1",
      "name": "dom1-o1" <- mine
    },
    {
      "domain": "sub1",
      "name": "sub1-o1" <- kid
    },
    {
      "domain": "sub2",
      "name": "sub2-o1" <- kid
    },
    {
      "domain": "sub1,sub2",
      "name": "common"  <- common
    }
  ]
}
